Sphenomorphus maindroni  is a species of lizard in the family Scincidae. The species was originally described by Sauvage in 1879. According to the Catalogue of Life, the species Sphenomorphus maindroni does not have known subspecies.The size of this specie is small, and the snoutâ€“vent length is between 24 and 59 mm; tail varies from nearly oval to square in cross-section.